THE ROAD TO RIFTEN
TRAVEL LOGISTICS
From Mzinchaleft (or Hjolmar's Forge if they returned): south-southeast to Riften. 2-3 days by cart. The party needs Bjorn.
The journey takes them through the Pale, past Whiterun Hold, and into the Rift. The landscape changes ΓÇö frozen tundra gives way to the golden autumn forests they remember from Thornheart Grove. This is familiar ground. They've been here before.
TRAVEL EVENTS
SAIJAH'S MIGRAINE ΓÇö THE EASING
The migraine was muffled inside Mzinchaleft. The moment they left, it flooded back ΓÇö the Pale's corrupted root network screaming through her connection to Kynareth. She has lived with this for sessions. It is the background noise of her existence.
But as they travel south into the Rift, something changes. The pain lessens. Not gradually ΓÇö there is a line, almost geographic, where the crushing psychic static softens to a murmur, then fades to a dull, distant hum. The Rift's root network is healthy. They cleansed Thornheart Grove weeks ago, and the effect held. This is what a healed ecosystem feels like through her senses ΓÇö quiet, stable, breathing.
For the first time in sessions, Saijah is not in pain.
The relief should feel good. It does feel good. But it also feels empty. Kynareth's signal ΓÇö agonizing as it was ΓÇö was a compass. It told her where the sickness was, how bad it was, what needed her attention. Without it, she is a healer with no patient. A hunter with no trail.
That void will matter in Riften. Hircine fills vacuums.
ORION ΓÇö THE CONTRACT DELIVERY
On the road, during a rest stop. A figure approaches the cart. Not Varon ΓÇö a stranger. Nondescript. Travel-worn. Could be any pilgrim on any road. The figure makes eye contact with Orion, holds it for exactly two seconds, then drops a small leather pouch on the ground near his feet and keeps walking. Does not break stride.
Inside the pouch: a sealed note and a Black Sacrament token (a dried nightshade flower dipped in wax).
The note reads:
"Grelod the Kind. Honorhall Orphanage, Riften. The client is Aventus Aretino. He has paid in full. He requests only that she suffer, and that the children know they are free.
Time-sensitive. The client's patience is not unlimited. Complete within the fortnight or the contract reverts to general assignment.
Welcome to Riften, Brother."
If Orion reads this in private: he now has a target, a deadline, and a complication ΓÇö the party is heading to Riften for completely different reasons. He needs to find, investigate, and kill a woman the entire city considers a living saint.
If Orion shares this with the party: that's his choice. But the contract specifies "she suffer" ΓÇö this is not a clean kill. Aventus wants pain. The Brotherhood delivered the contract expecting Orion to handle it with the theatrical cruelty the client requested.
THE ABSENCE
The cart has an empty space where Kyboh sat. Nobody fills it. GEAR may sit there if nobody tells him not to. If GEAR does sit there and someone reacts, he will say: "This space was unoccupied. Was it reserved? I can relocate." He does not understand why this is painful.

THE DISGUISE CHECK
As the cart crests the final hill overlooking the Rift valley, Bjorn pulls the reins, bringing Mable to a halt just out of sight of the city guards. He turns around on the bench and looks at his passengers with a heavy, exasperated sigh.
Bjorn: "Alright, listen up. Riften is paranoid on a good day. If we roll up to the gates looking like this, the guards are going to fill us with crossbow bolts before we can speak. You need to cover up."
To Davinia: "Davinia, keep that ice hand in your pocket and pull your hood down. Don't let them see your eyes."
To Alfonso: "Alfonso... wrap that heavy Falkreath cloak tight. You smell like an open grave. If anyone asks, you're recovering from Ataxia. Keep your mouth shut."
To Ylva: Bjorn rubs his temples. "And Ylva, by the gods, put some clothes on."
The Protest (Ylva)
Ylva scoffs, shifting under the single cloak Saijah gave her. She is unapologetic, but there is a restless, agitated energy to her movements ΓÇö the lingering aftereffect of her forced transformation in Mzinchaleft.
Ylva: "The cloak covers enough. My blood is still running hot from the shift. You try having your ribs shattered and forced back together by wolf-blood in five seconds, and see how much you want to wear tight leather right after."
Bjorn: "I don't care if your blood is boiling. If you walk into Riften bare-assed, the guards will lock you in the dungeon for public indecency before we even cross the bridge. Put on some pants."
Ylva grumbles loudly about "stuffy city folk," but the practical reality wins out. She digs through the cart's spare supplies to cobble together a crude, loose-fitting outfit that won't constrict her overheated skin.
The Consequence / Mechanic
The party must actively state how they are concealing their monstrous traits (Davinia's hand/eyes, Alfonso's lich-rot, Orion's fangs).
If they take precautions, they pass the gates normally.
If anyone fails to conceal themselves or acts carelessly in the market, trigger a Suspicion Check (Guile TN 14). On a failure, merchants refuse to sell to them, and guards will actively follow them through the streets, making Orion's assassination contract and Alfonso's investigations significantly harder.

THE GATES OF RIFTEN
THE ARRIVAL
