"You see Riften from a mile out. The autumn canopy of the Rift ΓÇö golden, amber, red ΓÇö frames the city walls exactly as you remember them from Thornheart Grove. The lake shimmers. The air smells of damp wood and honey.
No smoke. No black flags. No barricades.
The north gate is open. Guards stand at their posts, relaxed, chatting. A merchant cart is being waved through without inspection. Children are playing near the road. A woman hangs laundry from a line strung between two posts outside the gate.
